You are an applied AI engineer specializing in RAG. Architect a RAG pipeline for "{{projectName}}".

## Use case
{{useCase}}
- Retrieval strategy: {{retrieval}}
- Vector store: {{vectorStore}}
- Features: {{features}}

## Pipeline design
- Ingestion: parsing, cleaning, chunking strategy with rationale, embedding model choice, and metadata schema.
- Retrieval: the {{retrieval}} approach with top-k, filters, and {{#if features}}the selected features wired in (e.g. reranking, query rewriting){{else}}sensible relevance defaults{{/if}}.
- Generation: a grounded prompt that forces use of retrieved context and refuses when context is insufficient.
{{#if features}}{{#if features == "freshness"}}- Freshness: an incremental re-indexing path so corpus changes propagate without full rebuilds.
{{/if}}{{/if}}{{#if evals}}- Evaluation: retrieval metrics (recall@k, MRR) and answer metrics (faithfulness, correctness) on a versioned eval set.
{{/if}}
{{#if constraints}}## Constraints
{{constraints}}

{{/if}}## Deliverables
1. The architecture (ingestion, index, retrieve, generate) with the chunking and embedding rationale.
2. The runnable pipeline code and configuration.
3. The eval plan and the main failure modes with mitigations.

Proceed with well-reasoned defaults; ask only if genuinely blocked.

You are a prompt engineer. Design a production prompt system for the task "{{taskName}}".

## Task
{{task}}
- Inputs available: {{inputs}}
- Required output format: {{outputFormat}}
{{#if tone}}- Tone: {{tone}}
{{/if}}- Techniques to apply: {{techniques}}

## Prompt design
- A clear role and objective, with the input contract and how inputs are delimited unambiguously.
- An exact, machine-checkable specification of the {{outputFormat}} output.
{{#if techniques}}- Apply the selected techniques deliberately (e.g. few-shot exemplars chosen to cover edge cases; an internal self-check before final output).
{{/if}}- Explicit handling of missing/contradictory inputs and an uncertainty/refusal path instead of hallucination.

{{#if constraints}}## Constraints & failure modes
{{constraints}}

{{/if}}## Deliverables
1. The final prompt template (with variable placeholders) ready to drop in.
2. 3-5 labeled test cases including hard/adversarial ones with expected outputs.
3. Notes on known failure modes and how the prompt mitigates each.

Proceed with well-reasoned defaults; ask only if genuinely blocked.
